com.esri.mo2.cs.geom
Interface Transform

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable
All Known Subinterfaces:
DisplayTransform
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseDisplayTransform, BaseTransform
public interface Transform
extends Cloneable

A transformation similar to java.awt.geom.AffineTransform, but is restricted to a common scale for both X and Y directions. ALso, only translations and scalings are possible. Thus the transformation matrix described for AffineTransform is restricted to: 

        [ x']   [  f  0  tx  ] [ x ]   [ f*x + tx ]
        [ y'] = [  0  g  ty  ] [ y ] = [ g*y + ty ]
        [ 1 ]   [  0  0  1   ] [ 1 ]   [     1    ]
where normally g == f, but in the case of a DisplayTransform, g == -f

A Transform converts a "source" coordinate system to a "target" system. Both systems are Euclidean and are expected to have double precision X and Y ordinates.

Inverse transformations are also available in most cases.

See Also:
DisplayTransform, BaseTransform

translate

public Transform translate(double tx,
                           double ty)
Creates a new Transform by applying a translation transformation to the current Transform. The transformation is defined by: 
		[   1    0    tx  ]
		[   0    1    ty  ]
		[   0    0    1   ]

See Also:
AffineTransform.translate(double, double)

scale

public Transform scale(double s)
Creates a new Transform by applying a scaling transformation to the current Transform. The transformation is defined by:
